@{
    @foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
    {
        ViewData["Title"] = @brand.TitleTag;
    }
}

@section MetaTags {
    @foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
    {
        <meta name="keywords" content="@brand.MetaKeywords" />
        <meta name="description" content="@brand.MetaDescription" />
    }
}
@foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
{
    <div class=" ">
        <h1 class="latest-bike-head">@brand.BrandName Bikes</h1>
        @*<h2 class="latest-bike-description p-b20">@brand.Discription</h2>*@
        <div class="brand-info-container">
            <div class="brand-info-content">

                <h3>Yamaha Bikes in India 2025: Price, Mileage, Long Ride Picks & More</h3>

                <p class="brand-info-short">
                    Yamaha has long been synonymous with style, performance, and precision engineering. Originating in Japan, Yamaha Motor Company has carved out a legendary status in the global motorcycle scene — and it’s no different in India. Since entering the Indian market, Yamaha has consistently introduced bikes that appeal to both the urban commuter and the performance enthusiast.
                    From the iconic Yamaha FZ series to the sporty R15 lineup, the brand has balanced power with practicality. Yamaha's reputation is built on refined engines, eye-catching design, and a riding experience that speaks to passion rather than just practicality. In 2025, Yamaha’s portfolio in India continues to impress, offering a mix of street bikes, sportbikes, neo-retro models, and even a few performance-oriented scooters.
                    Here’s everything you need to know about Yamaha motorcycles in India, including the price list, mileage, best long-distance models, and why the brand continues to be a favorite among Indian riders.
                </p>

                <div class="brand-info-full" id="yamahaMoreText">
                    <h3>Yamaha Bikes Price List 2025 in India</h3>

                    <p>
                        Here is the updated Yamaha motorcycle price and mileage list for 2025:
                    </p>

                    <div class="brand-table-wrapper">
                        <table class="brand-info-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Model</th>
                                    <th>Ex-Showroom Price (₹)</th>
                                    <th>Mileage (km/l)</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>

                            <tbody>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha FZ FI</td>
                                    <td>₹1.17 lakh – ₹1.22 lakh</td>
                                    <td>45–50 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha FZS FI Deluxe</td>
                                    <td>₹1.23 lakh – ₹1.26 lakh</td>
                                    <td>46–50 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha FZ-X</td>
                                    <td>₹1.37 lakh – ₹1.42 lakh</td>
                                    <td>48–52 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha MT-15 V2</td>
                                    <td>₹1.69 lakh – ₹1.74 lakh</td>
                                    <td>40–45 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha R15 V4</td>
                                    <td>₹1.83 lakh – ₹1.90 lakh</td>
                                    <td>40–45 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha R15M</td>
                                    <td>₹1.95 lakh – ₹2.00 lakh</td>
                                    <td>38–43 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha Aerox 155 (scooter)</td>
                                    <td>₹1.47 lakh – ₹1.52 lakh</td>
                                    <td>40–45 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Yamaha R3 (expected 2025)</td>
                                    <td>₹4.20 lakh – ₹4.30 lakh</td>
                                    <td>25–30 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        <i>Note: Prices and mileage may vary depending on city, fuel type, riding conditions, and variant.</i>
                    </p>
                    <h3>Which Yamaha Is Best for Long Rides?</h3>

                    <p>
                        Yamaha is best known for its sporty DNA, but several models offer excellent comfort and features for long-distance travel. Whether it’s cruising down the highway or tackling a winding road trip, these bikes deliver on power, control, and comfort.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Top Yamaha Bikes for Touring in 2025:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Yamaha FZ-X</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>A neo-retro bike with relaxed ergonomics</li>
                                <li>Upright seating posture and plush seat</li>
                                <li>Best suited for city-to-highway transitions with smooth power delivery</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Yamaha MT-15 V2</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Lightweight, agile, and equipped with a 155cc liquid-cooled VVA engine</li>
                                <li>Great mid-range torque and upright stance</li>
                                <li>Excellent for solo travelers who want fun + practicality</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Yamaha R15M</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Sports bike lovers can enjoy long rides with its aerodynamic fairing and refined engine</li>
                                <li>Variable Valve Actuation (VVA) helps maintain power and efficiency at all speeds</li>
                                <li>Suitable for riders accustomed to aggressive riding posture</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Yamaha R3 (expected to launch in 2025)</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Twin-cylinder, liquid-cooled engine</li>
                                <li>Stable at high speeds with a comfortable seat for a sportbike</li>
                                <li>Ideal for touring and track-day versatility</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>
                    <h3>Which Yamaha Has the Best Mileage?</h3>

                    <p>
                        While Yamaha bikes are performance-driven, they’re also surprisingly fuel-efficient. Thanks to the brand’s Blue Core engine technology, Yamaha maximizes fuel combustion while reducing mechanical friction — translating to better efficiency.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Top Fuel-Efficient Yamaha Bikes:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Yamaha FZ-X</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mileage: 48–52 km/l</li>
                                <li>Perfect for urban riders who value comfort and economy</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Yamaha FZS FI Deluxe / FZ FI</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mileage: 45–50 km/l</li>
                                <li>Well-balanced power and efficiency</li>
                                <li>Comes with features like LED lighting and Bluetooth connectivity</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Yamaha Aerox 155 (Scooter)</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mileage: 40–45 km/l</li>
                                <li>A performance scooter with 14-inch wheels and powerful engine</li>
                                <li>Great for daily city runs and occasional fun rides</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        Yamaha’s mileage figures are highly competitive for the 150cc class, offering economy without compromising the riding thrill.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Why Is Yamaha Famous?</h3>

                    <p>
                        Yamaha’s fame goes far beyond just motorcycles — it’s a symbol of reliability, precision, and innovation. Here’s what makes Yamaha stand out in the Indian market:
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Reasons Yamaha Is So Popular:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Global Racing Heritage</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Yamaha’s involvement in MotoGP and other racing disciplines has helped translate track technology to street bikes.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Refined Engine Performance</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Yamaha engines are smooth, responsive, and tuned for long-term reliability.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Innovative Tech</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Features like Variable Valve Actuation (VVA), assist & slipper clutch, Bluetooth-enabled instrument clusters (Y-Connect), and LED DRLs are now standard in many models.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Aggressive Yet Timeless Designs</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Every Yamaha bike feels modern, sharp, and uniquely styled.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Wide Urban Appeal</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Yamaha continues to appeal to the youth with bikes that feel sporty, easy to ride, and reliable.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Strong After-Sales Service</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Yamaha’s extensive service network ensures riders get support and genuine parts across the country.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>
                    <h3>Final Thoughts</h3>

                    <p>
                        Yamaha’s 2025 motorcycle range in India proves that you don’t have to choose between performance and practicality. From the street-ready FZ series to the powerful and poised R15, Yamaha offers something for every type of rider.
                        Whether you’re a student, office commuter, or touring enthusiast, Yamaha’s lineup covers all needs with bikes that are stylish, efficient, and rewarding to ride. With exciting updates and a potential R3 launch, Yamaha continues to be a brand to watch in India’s premium commuter and performance motorcycle segments.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Top 10 FAQs About Yamaha Bikes in India (2025)</h3>

                    <div class="faq-container">

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>1. Which Yamaha bike gives the best mileage?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The Yamaha FZ-X delivers the best mileage at around 48–52 km/l.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>2. Is Yamaha R15M good for daily use?</h4>
                            <p>
                                It can be used daily, but its committed riding posture suits short rides better than long city commutes.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>3. Is Yamaha FZ a good bike for beginners?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes, Yamaha FZ FI is lightweight, easy to handle, and great for new riders.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>4. Which Yamaha is best for long-distance riding?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The Yamaha FZ-X and MT-15 V2 offer the most comfort and practicality for long trips.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>5. Is Yamaha MT-15 powerful enough for highways?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes, its 155cc engine with VVA performs well on highways with good mid-range torque.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>6. Does Yamaha make adventure bikes in India?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Currently, Yamaha doesn’t offer ADV bikes in India, but the FZ-X serves as a mild crossover.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>7. Are Yamaha bikes expensive to maintain?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Not really. Maintenance is affordable and service is widely available across India.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>8. Which is the best Yamaha scooter?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The Aerox 155 is Yamaha’s sportiest and most advanced scooter in India.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>9. What’s the expected launch date of Yamaha R3 in India?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yamaha R3 is expected to launch in 2025 in India as a CKD model with updated specs.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>10. Is Yamaha better for power or mileage?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yamaha strikes a solid balance — offering sporty performance without sacrificing too much fuel economy.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                    </div>



                </div>
                <button class="brand-read-btn"
                        onclick="toggleBrandInfo('yamahaMoreText', this)">
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <script>function toggleBrandInfo(contentId, button) {

                const content = document.getElementById(contentId);

                if (content.style.display === "block") {

                    content.style.display = "none";
                    button.innerText = "Read More";

                } else {

                    content.style.display = "block";
                    button.innerText = "Read Less";
                }
            }</script>
    </div>

}
@await Html.PartialAsync("_BrandComponent")
@await Html.PartialAsync("_AllComponent")